<item>
            <title>[SOLR-14219] OverseerSolrResponse&apos;s serialVersionUID has changed</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-14219</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When the &lt;tt&gt;useUnsafeOverseerResponse=true&lt;/tt&gt; option introduced in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-14095&quot; title=&quot;Replace Java serialization with Javabin in Overseer operations&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-14095&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-14095&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is used, the serialized OverseerSolrResponse has a different serialVersionUID to earlier versions, making it backwards-incompatible.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/lucene-solr/pull/1210&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/lucene-solr/pull/1210&lt;/a&gt; forces the serialVersionUID to its old value, so old and new nodes become compatible.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
