                            <comment id="17024249" author="andywebb1975" created="Mon, 27 Jan 2020 11:02:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We have a (non-production) cluster with three nodes - two are running 8.4.1, the third has 8.5.0 with &lt;tt&gt;useUnsafeOverseerResponse=true&lt;/tt&gt;. This simulates the situation we&apos;d have part-way through a rolling update in production.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If one of the 8.4.1 nodes is the overseer, requesting &lt;tt&gt;/solr/admin/collections?action=overseerstatus&lt;/tt&gt; on the other 8.4.1 node is OK, but on the 8.5.0 node it triggers an &lt;tt&gt;InvalidClassException&lt;/tt&gt;. If the 8.5.0 node is the overseer, that request to either of the 8.4.1 nodes triggers the exception.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;With the fix in the PR in place to force the new version of OverseerSolrResponse to have the same serialVersionUID as before, all three nodes&apos; overseers are compatible.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(NB an 8.4.0 node would not be compatible with earlier or newer versions due to its SolrResponse having a different UID - that&apos;s what led to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-14165&quot; title=&quot;SolrResponse serialVersionUID has changed&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-14165&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-14165&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
